Gunmen dressed in the uniform of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) have killed two persons and injured five others at Agulu Creek, Asari Toru Local Government Area, Rivers State. It was gathered that the gunmen, who operated on three 200 horsepower boats, opened fire on the victims  about 5pm on Sunday. The Rivers NSCDC command, in a statement signed by the Assistant Commandant, Oguntuase Michael, denied any involvement in the incident. “The NSCDC has nothing to do with the said attack,” Oguntuase said.